    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Performance Diagnostics - Test Procedures - 2. KOEO Standard Test
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010603.2" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="2">
        <title>2. KOEO Standard Test</title>
        <figure id="f305010609" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj31/j31096.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="592px"/>
            <caption></caption>
        </figure>
        <para id="tp305010602">
            <title>Purpose</title>
        </para>
        <para>To determine electrical malfunctions detected by the ECM self-test and Output Circuit Check (OCC)</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <title>Tools</title>
            <item>
                <para>EST with MasterDiagnostics&#174; software</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>EZ-Tech&#174; interface cable</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For CF only: If an EST is not available, see "
                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_54.xml" xrefid="s305010303.2.3.1">Standard Test Using Cruise Switches
                        (Except Stripped Chassis)
                    </hotlnk>
                    " in the "
                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050103.xml" xrefid="e3050103">Diagnostic Software Operation</hotlnk>
                    " section of this manual.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle, read all safety
                    instructions in the "Safety Information" section of this manual.
                </para>
            </warning>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid personal injury, use care to prevent contact with the door edge when the cab is up and
                    the door is open.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set parking brake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn ignition switch to ON. (Do not crank engine.)</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f305010610" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ31/J31044.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>KOEO Standard test</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select Diagnostics from the menu bar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select Key-On Engine-Off Tests from the drop down menu.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the KOEO Diagnostics menu, select Standard, then select Run to start the test.</para>
            <para>The ECM will complete an internal self-test and an OCC. When the OCC is completed, the DTC window will
                show DTCs, if there is a problem.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>This test initially takes up to 60 seconds. Look at the bottom of the diagnostic screen, the
                    screen will display Diagnostics Running while the test is running. Each subsequent test performed
                    without a key-off will take less than five seconds.
                </para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>When using the EST to do KOEO or KOER diagnostic tests, Standard test is always selected and run
                    first. If the ignition switch is not cycled, the Standard test does not have to be run again.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Record all DTCs on Diagnostic Form. See "
                <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050112.xml" xrefid="e3050112">Appendix B: Diagnostic Trouble Codes</hotlnk>
                " for a definition of the DTCs.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Correct problem causing active DTCs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clear DTCs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When finished with this test, continue with KOEO Injector Test.</para>
        </step1>
        <table id="t305010605" type="simple" frame="topbot">
            <title>Possible Causes</title>
            <tgroup cols="1">
                <colspec colname="col1"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>Failed electrical components or circuitry</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>OCC fault for the Injection Pressure Regulator (IPR) valve</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>OCC fault for the Inlet Air Heater (IAH) relay</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>OCC fault for the glow plug relay</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>OCC for fuel pump control</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>OCC fault for the Air Conditioning Control (ACC), this will not cause a hard start no
                                start condition.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
